Germany Doesn’t See Further EFSF Boost, Roesler Says

-- B y   T o n y   C z u c z k a
-- 
2011-09-30T06:23:35Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-30/germany-doesn-t-see-further-efsf-boost-roesler-says.html
German lawmakers won’t support any
further increase in its guarantees for the euro area’s rescue
fund, the European Financial Stability Facility, Economy
Minister Philipp Roesler said.  Parliament would have to approve any boost and “I don’t
see any inclination there to change the ceiling yet again, or to
increase the guarantees in some other way, for instance by
leveraging,” Roesler said on ARD television today.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Tony Czuczka at 
 aczuczka@bloomberg.net  